    name='search',
    response={
      'result': """A critical vulnerability, identified as CVE-2021-36260, has been found to affect Hikvision IP cameras through the `/SDK/webLanguage` path. This vulnerability is an unauthenticated command injection, enabling remote attackers to achieve arbitrary code execution with root privileges on affected devices.

The exploit works by sending a specially crafted HTTP PUT request to the `/SDK/webLanguage` endpoint. The request body contains an XML payload where the `<language>` tag's content is improperly sanitized and then passed to a `system()` call, leading to command execution. This flaw allows attackers to fully compromise the targeted devices and potentially extend their access to internal networks.

The vulnerability was discovered by Jacob Baines and was reported as being exploited in the wild. Hikvision released a security advisory on September 19, 2021, recommending immediate updates for versions older than 210628. Both Metasploit modules and Python Proof-of-Concept (PoC) scripts specifically target this vulnerability using the `/SDK/webLanguage` endpoint.

The `/SDK/webLanguage` path has also been observed in honeypot logs, indicating active scanning and exploitation attempts for this vulnerability."""
    }
  )
)] role='user'
