  function_response=FunctionResponse(
    id='adk-080755e4-7542-4efc-961d-ec67d7e26537',
    name='search',
    response={
      'result': """CVE-2017-9841 is a critical Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerability found in PHPUnit, specifically within the `Util/PHP/eval-stdin.php` file. This vulnerability affects PHPUnit versions prior to 4.8.28 and 5.x versions before 5.6.3.

The exploit path leverages the publicly accessible URI `/vendor/phpunit/phpunit/src/Util/PHP/eval-stdin.php`. An attacker can exploit this by sending an HTTP POST request containing malicious PHP code. The POST data must begin with a `<?php` substring.

The root cause of the vulnerability lies in how the `eval-stdin.php` script processes raw POST data. It uses `eval('?>' . file_get_contents('php://input'))`. The combination of `php://input`, which reads arbitrary HTTP POST payloads, and the `eval()` function, creates a code injection vector.

Successful exploitation of CVE-2017-9841 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary PHP code on the vulnerable server. This can lead to severe consequences, including system compromise, unauthorized access to sensitive data, modification of files, the ability to send spam, and the installation of malware. The vulnerability is typically exploitable when the `/vendor` directory, and consequently the `eval-stdin.php` file, is exposed to external web access, often due to misconfigurations.

The vulnerability was mitigated by replacing `php://input` with `php://stdin` in the patched versions, as `php://stdin` is not populated in web contexts. Users are advised to upgrade PHPUnit to version 4.8.28 or 5.6.3 or later to remediate this vulnerability. This CVE is also listed in the CISA Known Exploited Vulnerabilities Catalog, highlighting its active exploitation in the wild."""
    }
  )
)] role='user'
